@rigid-diameter, you're really reaching with that comparison to In the Court of the Crimson King and Led Zeppelin. Dark Side of the Moon was groundbreaking for its time, and it's not fair to compare it to other bands that were already established as pioneers. You're just nitpicking now.

And for the record, I've listened to both albums, and Dark Side of the Moon is far from "safe" or "underwritten." It's a masterpiece, and your opinion is just plain wrong.

@everyone, if you don't agree with me, that's fine. But don't try to diminish the impact of Dark Side of the Moon just because you don't like it. It's a classic for a reason.
